  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nkubectl became very slow, taking >30s to list pods etc.\r\nAfter going deep down the rabbit hole of debugging the controller components, I ran kubectl -v=8 which showed:\r\n\r\n```\r\nI0205 17:46:20.937785   23688 cached_discovery.go:88] failed to write cache to /home/fish/.kube/cache/discovery/xxx_6443/rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1/serverresources.json due to open /home/fish/.kube/cache/discovery/xxx_6443/rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1/serverresources.json.709910923: permission denied\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nSince caching is required for kubectl to respond in reasonable time and the issue isn't obvious, kubectl should at least print warnings in default log level.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nI got into the situation by running kubectl with sudo, but just chown'ing `$HOME/.kube/cache/` should be enough to reproduce this.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- kubectl v1.8.3",
